cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on peer-to-peer support for CDNs and the impact of ISP friendliness on traffic savings. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with on-demand streaming of long duration content. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are relevant as the paper studies the effects of partial participation and content availability on peer assistance. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses empirical data and investigates the effectiveness of different techniques for improving traffic gains.
